<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ881010-0035 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief -- Kerr-McGee Corp.: Purchase of Flag-Redfern Oil For $86 Million Is Arranged </HL><SO>  </SO><CO> KMG </CO><IN> TNM </IN><TEXT>   Kerr-McGee Corp. said it agreed to buy Flag-Redfern Oil Co., a Midland, Texas, oil and gas concern, for $86 million.    The transaction is subject to approval of Flag-Redfern's approximately 250 shareholders. The company is about 80%-owned by its board members and members of the Redfern family.    Kerr-McGee, an Oklahoma City energy concern, wouldn't elaborate on the transaction, saying that any comments would be premature. But Flag-Redfern said it had reserves of seven million barrels of oil and 39 billion cubic feet of natural gas at the end of 1987.    Flag-Redfern said two-thirds of its producing properties are in the Permian Basin of Texas, with the remainder in Oklahoma, Louisiana, Wyoming and New Mexico. </TEXT></DOC>